    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive setup, anchored by **Josh Lowe** (71.44) and **Gunnar Henderson** (68.74), who represent our strongest plays against favorable matchups. **Josh Lowe** is set to exploit a solid +14% platoon edge against Davis Martin, bolstered by a +5% wind-out factor that makes him the highest-ceiling option in the outfield. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** holds a significant +14% dynamic platoon advantage against Cam Schlittler; despite the pitcher\u2019s respectable skill level, **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s aggressive approach should pay dividends in a high-leverage spot. We are also closely tracking **Heliot Ramos** (65.97) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.92), both of whom benefit from weak SP_xERA marks, making them essential pillars for our scoring today.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the lineup optimizer involved **Coby Mayo**, who sat on the bubble with a score of 41.42. While his park factors are solid, his negative dynamic platoon split against Schlittler and the optimizer's preference for the higher-floor profiles of **Nolan Schanuel** and **Miguel Vargas** pushed him to the bench to preserve our limited game caps. Managers should remain cautious regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for almost every player; we have modeled our efficiency scores based on historical batting orders, but any major shift\u2014particularly for **Drake Baldwin** or **Sam Antonacci**\u2014could necessitate a reassessment. While we are running lean, note that **Luis Robert Jr.** remains on the IL, and we continue to monitor the status of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who is unavailable today due to a team off-day. Keep a close eye on the wind reports in games featuring **Nolan Schanuel** and **Miguel Vargas**, as the current \"Wind Out\" projections are providing the marginal lift required to keep these players in the starting rotation.",
